        <definition>uint32_t bt_iso_big_sync_param::mse</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>mse</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_iso_big_sync_param::mse</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Maximum subevents. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The MSE (Maximum Subevents) parameter is the maximum number of subevents that a Controller should use to receive data payloads in each interval for a BIS.</para>
<para>Value range is <ref refid="group__bt__iso_1gafef299e43e0f58ac23e1a1e75ccd0163" kindref="member">BT_ISO_SYNC_MSE_MIN</ref> to <ref refid="group__bt__iso_1gafd6e7b48394d6f6c8ddd485927b02b4b" kindref="member">BT_ISO_SYNC_MSE_MAX</ref>, or <ref refid="group__bt__iso_1ga47802144b8523b3d46af9ef97e744bbd" kindref="member">BT_ISO_SYNC_MSE_ANY</ref> to let the controller choose. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/bluetooth/iso.h" line="620" column="10" bodyfile="zephyr/bluetooth/iso.h" bodystart="620" bodyend="-1"/>
